{"first_name":"Dr. Nischal","last_name":"Piratla","permalink":"dr-nischal-piratla","crunchbase_url":"http://www.crunchbase.com/person/dr-nischal-piratla","homepage_url":"http://www.xerox.com/innovation/research-centre-india/nischal_piratla/enus.html","birthplace":"Hyderabad, India","twitter_username":"piratla","blog_url":"","blog_feed_url":"","affiliation_name":"Seagate","born_year":null,"born_month":null,"born_day":null,"tag_list":"","alias_list":null,"created_at":"Sat Jun 07 23:33:38 UTC 2008","updated_at":"Tue Oct 16 05:51:21 UTC 2012","overview":"<p>Nischal Piratla is Sr. Entrepreneur in Residence &amp; Area Manager (Distributed Computing &amp; Socio-Tech Design) at Xerox Research Centre, India. Before returning to India in 2010, he worked as Chief Scientist for Mobile Services &amp; Platforms, at Innovation Development with Deutsche Telekom, USA Lab, with a joint appointment at Deutsche Telekom Labs (T-Labs), Berlin, Germany. He was also associated with the Department of Computer Science, UC  Santa Barbara as Adjunct Associate Professor.\nHe started at T-Labs, Berlin in 2005 as a Senior Research Scientist, and within a year founded its first spin-off, Qiro GmbH, and led it as CTO. After the exit, returned to T-Labs as Chief Technologist with a short term Visiting Scholarship at Stanford University. His previous terms at industry also include Lucent/Avaya Inc. (2000-2002), Seagate (1999-2000) and CMC (1996-97).</p>\n\n<p>Nischal considers his knowledge/skills in Mathematics and his field of expertise, namely, Networking, Mobile Services, Recommendation Systems and HCI as tools, which when properly brewed with intuition and business logic lead to fascinating innovations. He has formed and worked with teams from more than ten countries. His expertise in technology, ability to go across domains, knowledge of global work cultures, and intuitive acumen for business makes him an exciting entrepreneur.  He believes that a researcher with entrepreneurial spirit brings a very interesting dimension to industry research.</p>\n\n<p>Nischal holds 1 patent and has 20 pending applications in USA, Germany, Israel and India. He has published various technical papers in international conferences and journals, and also has an IETF RFC to his credit. He is a Senior Member of IEEE.</p>","image":{"available_sizes":[[[117,150],"assets/images/resized/0002/4732/24732v2-max-150x150.jpg"],[[195,250],"assets/images/resized/0002/4732/24732v2-max-250x250.jpg"],[[351,450],"assets/images/resized/0002/4732/24732v2-max-450x450.jpg"]],"attribution":""},"degrees":[{"degree_type":"PhD","subject":"Electrical Engineering","institution":"Colorado St. University","graduated_year":2005,"graduated_month":null,"graduated_day":null},{"degree_type":"MS","subject":"Electrical Engineering","institution":"Colorado St. University","graduated_year":1999,"graduated_month":null,"graduated_day":null},{"degree_type":"B.Tech","subject":"Electronics and Communications","institution":"JNTU College of Engineering","graduated_year":1996,"graduated_month":null,"graduated_day":null}],"relationships":[{"is_past":false,"title":"Sr. Entrepreneur in Residence","firm":{"name":"Xerox Research Centre India","permalink":"xerox-research-centre-india","type_of_entity":"company","image":null}},{"is_past":true,"title":"Co-Founder & CTO","firm":{"name":"Qiro","permalink":"qiro","type_of_entity":"company","image":{"available_sizes":[[[150,75],"assets/images/resized/0002/0138/20138v1-max-150x150.png"],[[220,111],"assets/images/resized/0002/0138/20138v1-max-250x250.png"],[[220,111],"assets/images/resized/0002/0138/20138v1-max-450x450.png"]],"attribution":null}}},{"is_past":true,"title":"Chief Technologist (Mobile Arch. & Services","firm":{"name":"Deutsche Telekom Labs","permalink":"deutsche-telekom-labs","type_of_entity":"company","image":{"available_sizes":[[[150,44],"assets/images/resized/0002/3118/23118v1-max-150x150.png"],[[182,54],"assets/images/resized/0002/3118/23118v1-max-250x250.png"],[[182